item.description:
To my Italian friends, except for Lorenzo who said he enjoyed this and didn&rsquo;t seem to be lying, you may look away.
&hellip;
This is adapted from the New York Times&rsquo; &ldquo;drunken pasta&rdquo;, or pasta alla chiantigiana. It has become a favourite of our home — part of my repertoire. It takes a little longer than most tomato-based sauces to cook because it requires simmering an almost-full bottle of red wine.
